article.headline: Indiana St. 69, Missouri St. 52
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. -- Carl Richard had 20 points and 10 rebounds to lead four Sycamores in double figures as Indiana State beat Missouri State 69-52 in its regular-season finale Saturday. Jay Tunnell scored 16, Harry Marshall 12 and Aaron Carter 11 for Indiana State (10-20, 7-11 Missouri Valley). Cardell McFarland, with 12, was the only player in double figures for the Bears (11-19, 3-15), who led 32-31 at the break before being outscored 38-20 in the second half. The Sycamores scored 19 points off Missouri State turnovers and outrebounded the Bears 30-17. Indiana State scored 16 second-chance points compared with the Bears' five. The game included nine ties and 10 lead changes. Indiana State's largest lead was by 21 with 3:30 left in the game.
